<searchtitle>imaserver show ConnectionPolicy</searchtitle>
</titlealts>
<prolog><metadata>
<keywords><indexterm>show ConnectionPolicy</indexterm></keywords>
</metadata></prolog>
<refbody>
<section><title>Purpose</title>Shows the configuration details of
a specified connection policy.</section>
<section><title>Syntax</title><ph
conref="../../TextEntities.dita#TextEntities/imaservercmd"></ph> <cmdname>show
ConnectionPolicy "Name=</cmdname><varname>policyName</varname><cmdname>"</cmdname></section>
<section><title>Parameters</title><dl><dlentry>
<dt><varname>policyName</varname></dt>
<dd>Specifies the name of the connection policy that you want to view
the configuration details of.</dd>
</dlentry></dl></section>
<section><title>Usage <tm tmclass="IGNORE" tmtype="reg" trademark="Notes">Notes</tm></title><ul>
<li>The command must be capitalized as shown.</li>
<li>The command must use the double quotation marks as shown.</li>
<li>Use the <cmdname>imaserver list ConnectionPolicy</cmdname> command
to view a list of all the connection policies on <ph
conref="../../TextEntities.dita#TextEntities/ISM"></ph>.</li>
</ul></section>
